(Atho is a post-quantum-oriented UTXO blockchain built around deterministic consensus behavior,) Tj
T*
(explicit policy constants, and production-aware runtime controls. The protocol combines) Tj
T*
(Falcon-512 signatures, SHA3-384 identity and hashing surfaces, compact binary transaction) Tj
T*
(transport, integer-atom accounting, and an integrated private transaction subsystem \(Platinum) Tj
T*
(Shield\) that introduces commitment/nullifier/anchor mechanics with block-level proof gating. The) Tj
T*
(design goal is not to maximize any single headline metric; it is to maximize coherence between) Tj
T*
(policy, code, operational controls, and economic modeling.[^1][^2]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This whitepaper provides a full technical account of current Atho design and implementation) Tj
T*
(posture. It explains deterministic key and address derivation, transaction serialization and) Tj
T*
(validation, payment-only proof-of-work block acceptance, simplified miner-fee routing, storage) Tj
T*
(and reorg semantics, binary pinning/runtime guard controls, API permissions and operator) Tj
T*
(hardening, and attack-surface outcomes from sandbox audit harnesses. The paper also maps policy) Tj
T*
(claims to code surfaces and generated artifacts so reviewers can verify claims through) Tj
T*
(repository evidence rather than narrative assertions alone.[^3][^4]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The key thesis is that trust in a blockchain system should be evaluated as an engineering) Tj
T*
(output, not a marketing posture. In practical terms, this requires strict integer accounting,) Tj
T*
(replay boundaries, deterministic serialization, public/private state safety, and reproducible) Tj
T*
(economics. Atho?s v3 technical baseline is organized around those constraints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
