(- Design Principles and System Objectives) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho?s design is built around principled constraints rather than feature accumulation. The) Tj
T*
(following objectives determine architecture and policy decisions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2.1 Determinism as a Security Primitive) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Consensus safety is treated as a deterministic execution problem. Determinism reduces the) Tj
T*
(probability that logically equivalent transactions or blocks are interpreted differently across) Tj
T*
(nodes due to parser ambiguity, non-canonical encodings, floating-point drift, or hidden) Tj
T*
(compatibility branches.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho applies determinism through:) Tj
T*
(- Integer-only atom accounting in consensus-critical value math.) Tj
T*
(- Canonical no-witness signing digest reconstruction.) Tj
T*
(- Bounded signature/public-key byte policy checks.) Tj
T*
(- Network domain checks in tx/network admission.) Tj
T*
(- Deterministic role-derived address semantics.) Tj
T*
(- Deterministic lockup state transition checks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In this model, ?policy clarity? is not documentation polish; it is a correctness requirement.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2.2 Explicit Policy Over Implicit Behavior) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Protocol constants are treated as hard-coded consensus policy with runtime invariants. Changes) Tj
T*
(are by definition consensus changes and therefore governance events. This framing reduces) Tj
T*
(discretionary ambiguity, especially in monetary and lockup logic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key explicit policy categories include:) Tj
T*
(- Block cadence, retarget windows, and maturity thresholds.) Tj
T*
(- Fee floor and minimum fee constants.) Tj
T*
(- Block/base/weight caps and transaction policy size.) Tj
T*
(- Reward schedule and daily decay rules.) Tj
T*
(- Hard max supply and zero-premine constraints.) Tj
T*
(- Confirmation, maturity, and fee-policy boundaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2.3 Separation of Roles and Domains) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho separates domains at cryptographic and transaction layers:) Tj
T*
(- Signing identity \(Falcon\) and encryption/encapsulation identity \(Kyber\) use separated) Tj
T*
(derivation contexts.) Tj
T*
(- Payment addresses and private bundle identities derive from distinct domain tags.) Tj
T*
(- Mining eligibility is proof-of-work based and no longer depends on bond/stake side state.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This reduces cross-context confusion and constrains replay surfaces.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2.4 Operational Realism) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho assumes many failures occur in deployment and runtime governance, not only in abstract) Tj
T*
(consensus logic. The stack therefore includes binary pinning, strict canonical binary paths,) Tj
T*
(runtime guard modes, and release manifest verification controls. This operational lens is a core) Tj
T*
(system property, not an optional appendix.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
