(Therefore policy changes must be treated as coordinated consensus+operations events.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(---) Tj
T*
(- Architecture Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho uses a layered architecture that keeps orchestration and operator ergonomics in Python) Tj
T*
(while relocating performance-critical loops and specialized cryptographic operations into native) Tj
T*
(binaries.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.1 Layer 0: Binary Runtime and Pinning) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Native binaries are expected in canonical per-platform directories under) Tj
T*
(Binaries/<platform-tag>/, with SHA3-384 metadata tracked in pin registries. Strict mode can) Tj
T*
(require canonical path and hash matches before runtime loading proceeds. This control limits) Tj
T*
(accidental runtime drift and supply-chain substitution risk in production-like environments.[^8]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4.2 Layer 1: Cryptography Runtime) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Falcon keygen/sign/verify operations are exposed through CLI wrappers and optional in-process) Tj
T*
(verify acceleration where configured. This layer is bounded by explicit byte policies and) Tj
T*
(hash-pin checks. The objective is cryptographic determinism across environments, not ad hoc) Tj
T*
